💰 Finance Module — Table List, Purpose & Future Mapping
1. fin_invoices

Purpose:
Stores invoices generated for clients. Supports contract billing, manual billing, and proposal conversion.

Future Mapping:

client_id → crm_clients.id
contract_id → crm_contracts.id
proposal_id → crm_proposals.id
created_by → users.id

Used With:

fin_invoice_items
fin_payments
fin_credit_notes
2. fin_invoice_items

Purpose:
Stores line items within invoices (percentage billing, flat fee, setup fee, add-ons).

Future Mapping:

invoice_id → fin_invoices.id

Used For:

Invoice subtotal calculation
Service breakdown
3. fin_credit_notes

Purpose:
Stores credit adjustments applied to invoices (refunds, discounts, write-offs).

Future Mapping:

invoice_id → fin_invoices.id
client_id → crm_clients.id
created_by → users.id

Used For:

Reduce invoice balance
Refund tracking
4. fin_payments

Purpose:
Stores incoming payments from clients.

Future Mapping:

client_id → crm_clients.id
bank_account_id → fin_bank_accounts.id
payment_method_id → payment_methods.id
created_by → users.id

Used With:

fin_payment_allocations
fin_transactions
5. fin_payment_allocations

Purpose:
Maps payments to invoices (supports partial and multi-invoice payments).

Future Mapping:

payment_id → fin_payments.id
invoice_id → fin_invoices.id

Use Case:

One payment → multiple invoices
One invoice → multiple payments
6. payment_methods (existing table — will reuse)

Purpose:
Defines payment types (ACH, Wire, Check, Stripe, etc.)

Used By:

fin_payments
